    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-16T11:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-16T11:05:00-05:00" n="133"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d133">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23599: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Mazatlán</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mazatlán</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-16T09:00:00-07:05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1920—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government of Sinaloa and practically all of the State officials arrived at
                    Mazatlán by special train from Culiacán at 6 this morning transferring capital
                    [of] State to Mazatlán, having no means of defense against General Ángel Flores
                    who is rapidly moving this way from the north.</p>
                <p>This practically leaves all of Sinaloa except city of Mazatlán in the hands
                    rebels. Flores rushing this way to take Mazatlán before General Diéguez can
                    reach here, latter being due about 19th.</p>
                <p>As the communication with Department likely to be cut off any moment, suggest
                    that naval vessel stand by to protect American interests and assure continued
                    communication.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
